			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Well there are some problems with the above post. Thanks to our friends at Verant, the damage on who gets the kill is not group based but personal based. Group or not group, if that wizard can hit harder then any one person in your group then he gets the kill. Example: Your group puts out 200Damage a round, and each person in the group puts out 50 damage and there are 4 people. Well One wizard can take the kill that hits for 51 damage a round =)<BR>
<BR>
I dont know if this has changed recently by a patch, but it can be very upsetting when my group puts out 500+ damage a round and one kill stealer that only puts out 200 damage a round gets the kill.<BR>
<BR>
What you mentioned about invis, wizards cannot cast spells while invis, nor can they loot while invis.<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
